        "---\n",
        "title: \"Business Running Case: Building a Section-Scoped RAG System for SEC 10-K (2024)\"\n",
        "subtitle: \"Project Instructions II\"\n",
        "number-sections: true\n",
        "date: \"2024-11-21\"\n",
        "date-modified: today\n",
        "date-format: long\n",
        "categories: [\"Project\", \"RAG\", \"SEC 10-K\", \"Embeddings\", \"LLM Systems\"]\n",
        "description: \"In this project, you will build a simple Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) notebook that works over a small, domain-scoped subset of SEC 10-K data. This is a controlled prototype to help you understand the mechanics of RAG pipelines before building a larger system in Project 3.\"\n",
        "execute:\n",
        "  echo: true\n",
        "  eval: false\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Objective and Context\n",
        "\n",
        "Each team will build a [*simple Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) notebook*]{.uublue-bold} over a [*small, domain-scoped SEC 10-K corpus*]{.uublue-bold}. This is [*not*]{.uublue-bold} yet the full enterprise RAG system. Instead, this project is a [*controlled prototype*]{.uublue-bold} that helps your team learn how a retrieval pipeline works before you build the larger system in Project 3.\n",
        "\n",
        "Your team will begin from the [*smaller extracted subset*]{.uublue-bold} created in the previous step. Rather than indexing the full 10-K filing, you will work with a focused dataset such as:\n",
        "\n",
        "- [*AI investment / AI strategy*]{.uublue-bold}\n",
        "- [*Human capital / workforce*]{.uublue-bold}\n",
        "- [*Data center / infrastructure*]{.uublue-bold}\n",
        "- another approved narrow domain extracted from the filing\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is to build a notebook that can:\n",
        "\n",
        "* embed the selected document chunks\n",
        "* store them in a vector index\n",
        "* retrieve relevant chunks for a question\n",
        "* generate an answer using an LLM\n",
        "* evaluate the quality of the retrieval and response\n",
        "\n",
        "You can use the Following 3 notebooks (already shared with you) as references for how to build this prototype:\n",
        "\n",
        "- [Simple RAG](https://drive.google.com/file/d/16UeBOPyVHFv1sdhioOR2-KiZSJ87fpBO/view?usp=drive_link)\n",
        "- [Simple RAG With Reranking](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1xTfyvqNxej_C6nXZvYiVsZI2zSwIyv1X/view?usp=drive_link)\n",
        "- [RAG with LangSmith](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1uwQz7JjOUU2xvvXQfKNIht9xO2v6qeRx/view?usp=drive_link)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-important}\n",
        "This project is intentionally scoped to a [*notebook interface in Google Colab*]{.uublue-bold}. A chatbot interface is [*not required*]{.uublue-bold}. You are being asked to understand the mechanics of a RAG pipeline over a well-scoped financial document subset. The quality of your retrieval logic, grounding discipline, and evaluation matters more than interface complexity.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# Key Takeaways\n",
        "\n",
        "By completing this project, your team should understand:\n",
        "\n",
        "- A RAG pipeline works end-to-end\n",
        "- [*small domain-scoped corpora*]{.uublue-bold} often perform better than unfiltered full-document corpora\n",
        "- [*Embeddings*]{.uublue-bold} influence retrieval quality\n",
        "- [*Compare local/open models and API-based models*]{.uublue-bold}\n",
        "- [*Evaluate*]{.uublue-bold} whether an answer is actually grounded in retrieved evidence\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Project Scope\n",
        "\n",
        "## What You Will Build\n",
        "\n",
        "You will build a [*simple notebook-based RAG pipeline*]{.uublue-bold} that works over a [*small extracted SEC 10-K dataset*]{.uublue-bold}. Your notebook should include:\n",
