        "# Platform and Model Options\n",
        "\n",
        "You may choose [*one*]{.uublue-bold} of the following generation approaches, You may run these using Hugging Face Transformers, sentence-transformers, or another approved inference method compatible with Colab:\n",
        "\n",
        "- API-based models (preffered)\n",
        "    - OpenAI\n",
        "    - Gemini\n",
        "    - Claude\n",
        "- Local/open models from Hugging Face\n",
        "    - Mistral\n",
        "    - BAAI\n",
        "    - Qwen\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Embedding Options\n",
        "\n",
        "You may choose embedding models:\n",
        "\n",
        " - sentence-transformers models\n",
        " - BAAI embedding models\n",
        " - OpenAI embeddings\n",
        " - Gemini-compatible embedding flow if available\n",
        "\n",
        "## Your team must clearly state:\n",
        "\n",
        "* which embedding model was used\n",
        "* which generation model was used\n",
        "* why that choice was appropriate for your domain and compute budget\n",
        "\n",
        "# Overall Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "```{dot}\n",
        "digraph RAGPipeline {\n",
        "    rankdir=LR;\n",
        "    node [shape=box, style=rounded];\n",
        "\n",
        "    A [label=\"Filtered SEC 10-K Domain Corpus\"];\n",
        "    B [label=\"Chunked Documents\"];\n",
        "    C [label=\"Embedding Model\"];\n",
        "    D [label=\"Vector Index\"];\n",
        "    E [label=\"User Question\"];\n",
        "    F [label=\"Top-k Retrieval\"];\n",
        "    G [label=\"Context Assembly\"];\n",
        "    H [label=\"LLM Generation\"];\n",
        "    I [label=\"Grounded Answer + Evaluation\"];\n",
        "\n",
        "    A -> B -> C -> D;\n",
        "    E -> F;\n",
        "    D -> F -> G -> H -> I;\n",
        "}\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the Project Notebook\n",
        "\n",
        "Create a notebook in your project folder.\n",
        "\n",
        "- `project2_rag_notebook.ipynb`\n",
        "  - code\n",
        "  - outputs\n",
        "  - explanation\n",
        "  - interpretation\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the Small Extracted Domain Corpus\n",
        "\n",
        "Load the filtered dataset from the previous step.\n",
        "\n",
        "* `ai_filtered_chunks.csv`\n",
        "* `human_capital_chunks.parquet`\n",
        "* `datacenter_chunks.csv`\n",
        "\n",
        "Your notebook should briefly describe:\n",
        "\n",
        "* what domain was selected\n",
        "* which SEC Items were used\n",
        "* how the smaller subset was produced\n",
        "* why this scope is appropriate for a simple RAG prototype\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Inspect the Corpus Before Embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "Before embedding, inspect the data. At minimum, show:\n",
        "\n",
        "* number of chunks\n",
        "* sections included\n",
        "* average token length\n",
        "* sample chunks\n",
        "\n",
        "Discuss:\n",
        "\n",
        "* whether the chunks look coherent\n",
        "* whether the extraction seems too broad or too narrow\n",
        "* whether your domain terms are well represented\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Build the Embedding Layer\n",
        "\n",
        "Generate embeddings for your chunked documents. Your notebook must show:\n",
        "\n",
        "* embedding model selected\n",
        "* how the embeddings are created\n",
        "* the dimension of the embedding vectors\n",
        "* the shape of the resulting embedding matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "Explain:\n",
        "\n",
        "* why this embedding model was chosen\n",
        "* whether it is local/open or API-based\n",
        "* any compute trade-offs\n",
        "\n",
        "# Build the Vector Store / Retrieval Index\n",
        "\n",
        "Store the embeddings in a retrieval structure such as:\n",
        "\n",
        "* FAISS\n",
        "* Chroma\n",
        "\n",
        "You must demonstrate:\n",
        "\n",
        "* that the index was created successfully\n",
        "* that queries can retrieve relevant chunks\n",
        "* the value of `top_k` you selected\n",
        "\n",
        "You should explain:\n",
        "\n",
        "* why `top_k` was chosen\n",
        "* what happens if retrieval returns too few or too many chunks\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Implement the Simple RAG Generation Step\n",
        "\n",
        "Build a simple pipeline:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. accept a user question\n",
        "2. retrieve top-k chunks\n",
        "3. assemble context\n",
        "4. send that context to the LLM\n",
        "5. generate an answer\n",
        "\n",
        "This can be done with:\n",
        "\n",
        "* plain Python functions\n",
        "* LangChain\n",
        "* a simplified RAG workflow inspired by the example notebooks\n",
        "\n",
        "You do [*not*]{.uublue-bold} need a chatbot. A few notebook query cells are sufficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ask Structured Domain Questions\n",
        "\n",
        "Your team must test the notebook with [*at least 8–10 questions*]{.uublue-bold} that fit the selected domain.\n",
        "\n",
        "Examples for AI domain:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Does the company describe AI as a strategic investment area?\n",
        "* Is AI framed as operational efficiency, innovation, or risk?\n",
        "* Are AI-related expenditures or R&D activities discussed?\n",
        "* Does the company mention AI-related uncertainty or regulatory concerns?\n",
        "\n",
        "Examples for human capital domain:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Does the company identify labor shortages as a risk?\n",
        "* Is workforce development described as a strategic priority?\n",
        "* Are compensation or retention issues mentioned?\n",
        "\n",
        "Examples for data center / infrastructure domain:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Does the company discuss investment in data centers or cloud infrastructure?\n",
        "* Is infrastructure linked to scaling digital services?\n",
        "* Are data center or compute demands framed as cost drivers?\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show Retrieval Outputs Explicitly\n",
        "\n",
        "For each sample query, show:\n",
        "\n",
        "* the question\n",
        "* retrieved chunks\n",
        "* chunk scores if available\n",
        "* chunk metadata\n",
        "* generated answer\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evaluate the RAG System\n",
        "\n",
        "Your notebook must include a simple evaluation section. You do [*not*]{.uublue-bold} need a perfect benchmark, but you must evaluate the system in a structured way.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Minimum required evaluation dimensions\n",
        "\n",
        "### Retrieval Relevance\n",
        "\n",
        "For a small set of test questions:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Were the retrieved chunks relevant?\n",
        "* Did retrieval capture the right domain evidence?\n",
        "\n",
        "This can be done manually using a small table.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Grounding\n",
        "\n",
        "Check whether the answer is actually supported by the retrieved chunks.\n",
        "\n",
        "Questions to ask:\n",
        "\n",
        "* Did the answer rely only on retrieved evidence?\n",
        "* Did the answer introduce unsupported claims?\n",
        "\n",
        "### Failure Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "Identify at least [*3 failure cases*]{.uublue-bold} such as:\n",
        "\n",
        "* weak retrieval\n",
        "* irrelevant chunk returned\n",
        "* answer too vague\n",
        "* answer hallucinated beyond retrieved context\n",
        "* domain filtering too broad or too narrow\n",
        "\n",
        "## Optional advanced evaluation\n",
        "\n",
        "If your team wants, you may use ideas from the example notebooks such as:\n",
        "\n",
        "* RAGAS-style evaluation\n",
        "* faithfulness/relevance checks\n",
        "* LangSmith-style tracing\n",
        "\n",
        "These are optional enhancements, not required for baseline credit.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reflect on Design Trade-Offs\n",
        "Your notebook must include a discussion of:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "* why working on a small filtered corpus helped retrieval\n",
        "* what limitations remain\n",
        "* whether local/open models performed differently from API-based models\n",
        "* how this notebook should evolve into a full system in Project 3\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
